methods.Comparator comparator(): Returns the comparator used to order the keys in this map, or null if this map uses the natural ordering of its keys.
methods.Set entrySet(): Returns a Set view of the mappings contained in this map.
methods.K firstKey(): Returns the first (lowest) key currently in this map.
methods.SortedMap headMap(K toKey): Returns a view of the portion of this map whose keys are strictly less than toKey.
methods.Set keySet(): Returns a Set view of the keys contained in this map.
methods.K lastKey(): Returns the last (highest) key currently in this map.
methods.SortedMap subMap(K fromKey, K toKey): Returns a view of the portion of this map whose keys range from fromKey, inclusive, to toKey, exclusive.
methods.SortedMap tailMap(K fromKey): Returns a view of the portion of this map whose keys are greater than or equal to fromKey.
methods.Collection values(): Returns a Collection view of the values contained in this map.
